gists, environmentalists, planners, and others concerned with the fate of the earth. This book brings together original essays by leading experts who reflect on Teilhard’s legacy for today’s globalized world. They explore such topics as: the idea of God and the person; quantum reality and Teilhard’s vision; spiritual resources for the future; politics and economics; and a charter for co-evolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh1 aBoissonnat, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamdessus, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Thomas M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadelin, Henri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeynard, Thierry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeynard, Thierry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRockefeller, Steven C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchäfer, Lothar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTucker, Mary Evelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831107072980 cprintz978082322690040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329273840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823292738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823292738/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL 